  <Docs>
    <summary>Provides arguments for customizing a typeface when creating a font.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

<xref:T:SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments> is a `ref struct` that bundles options passed to <xref:M:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone*> to select a font variation, palette, or collection index.

## Examples

```csharp
var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    CollectionIndex = 0,
    PaletteIndex = 1,
    VariationDesignPosition = new[]
    {
        new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate { Axis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght"), Value = 700 }
    }
};
using var typeface = SKTypeface.FromFile("MyFont.ttf").Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
